       4/4 - Eddie Butler looks at the symbols and ideas we've chosen to 
       represent us for the past 6,000 years, give or take a decade. 
       Everything from the red dragon to the red flag and from ancient 
       burial mounds to the iPod. And it's not just one way traffic into 
       Wales. Eddie learns about a community in India that still sings 
       Welsh hymns, Hen Wlad Fy Nhadau is their anthem, and they prefer 
       lamb with mint sauce to a curry!
